\cf0 Add the broth to the onions in the slow-cooker, cover and cook on high until hot. Preheat the broiler to high with the rack in the upper third of the oven. Divide the soup among six oven proof bowls. Top each with a slice of bread and add several tablespoons of cheese. Place the bowls on a rimmed baking sheet and broil until only the cheese is bubbling. Serve immediately.\

